						               													<description>Three-Player Crokinole is a specially designed Crokinole board that works only with three. This game cannot be played on a standard board and thus is considered to be a different game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The three-player board has markings that divide the board into three areas (vs four for a standard board), and repositions the pegs around the center to make these three positions optimal for shooting. Three players play independently (no partners), and when shooting either other player's disk must be hit for your shot to be legal. Scoring is done on a differences basis as in the original game, except often two people will score per turn as a result.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
